cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a two-step approach for day-ahead hourly scheduling in a distribution system operation, which involves minimizing operation costs and system loss. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The stochastic optimization and Gaussian mixture model used for forecasting can be considered as AI techniques.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The Gaussian mixture model used for forecasting can also be considered as a machine learning technique.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a distributed optimization approach based on the alternating direction method of multiplier (ADMM) for solving the nonconvex optimization problem. This falls under the domain of distributed computing.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): While not the main focus of the paper, the implementation of the proposed approach would require software engineering skills and considerations.
